      "text": [
        " عَلِيٌّ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"اَلْمُضَارِبُ مَا أَنْفَقَ فِي سَفَرِهِ فَهُوَ مِنْ جَمْعِ اَلْمَالِ فَإِذَا قَدِمَ بَلْدَتَهُ فَمَا أَنْفَقَ فَهُوَ مِنْ نَصِيبِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3846 - Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said:\n\"Whatever the partner spends during his travel is taken from the joint capital. However, when he returns to his town, whatever he spends is from his own share.\""
        ]
      }
    },
